rowing armies and prepare for the coming of C\'Thun.\n',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),(10834,'%s examines the Scourgestone closely.','',2,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),(10835,'The evil in these stones is strong, but it has been dispelled.','',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),(10836,'','This can\'t be right. An Old God could never be allowed to enter this world. The results would be... Oh dear!',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),(10837,'','%s regains her composure.',2,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),(10838,'','There is more.',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),(10839,'','The moment that C\'Thun had so patiently waited for had finally arrived. His children had spent thousands of years building an army capable of exacting revenge upon the whole of Kalimdor and now the prize was within their grasp.\n',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),(10840,'','The Titans had long since vacated this world. Only the night elves that once inhabited this area were here to defend. Oh my! The next passage is fascinating!\n',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),(10841,'','A mighty Qiraji known as General Rajaxx would command the initial incursion into Silithus. Only one would stand in his way: A night elf known as Staghelm. They refer to him as Khar\'sis or \'hand of the earth\' in the native Qiraji tongue.\n',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),(10842,'','Staghelm and his armies were clearly overwhelmed as the endless flow of Rajaxx\'s troops poured into Silithus. It would seem as if Staghelm, however, was more than just a nuisance to the Qiraji. Under Staghelm, the whole of the night elf armies had come together to defend Kalimdor, greatly slowing the Qiraji forces.\n',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),(10843,'','Unfortunately, the night elf defense was untenable and Rajaxx knew that they could not hold out much longer. Their tenacity, however, was causing great frustration to Rajaxx and causing even more frustration to his king. Wait, kings? Incredible...\n',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),(10844,'','Vek\'nilash and Vek\'lor, known as the Twin Emperors of Ahn\'Qiraj, watched the war from the sanctuary of their temple. The clever brothers devised a